\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'Give those to Dean,' I said.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 Harry blinked like someone awakening from a momentary doze, saw Percy's gun and stick still in his hands, and passed them over to Dean. Coffey, meanwhile, hulked in the corridor with his bald skull almost brushing one of the caged overhead lights. Standing there with his hands in front of him and his shoulders sloped forward to either side of his barrel chest, he made me think again, as I had the first time I saw him, of a huge captured bear.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'Lock Percy's toys in the duty desk until we get back,' I said.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'If we get back,' Harry added.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'I will,' Dean said to me, taking no notice of Harry.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'And if someone shows up—probably no one will, but if someone does—what do you say?'\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'That Coffey got upset around midnight,' Dean said. He looked as studious as a college student taking a big exam. 'We had to give him the jacket and but him in the restraint room. If there's noise, who ever hears it'll just think it's him.' He raised his chin to John Coffey.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'And what about us?' Brutal asked.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'Paul's over in Admin, pulling Del's file and going over the witnesses,' Dean said. 'It's especially important this time, because the execution was such a balls-up. He said he'd probably be there the rest of the shift. You and Harry and Percy are over in the laundry, washing your clothes.'\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 Well, that was what folks said, anyway. There was a crap-game in the laundry supply room some nights; on others it was blackjack or poker or acey-deucey. Whatever it was, the guards who participated were said to be washing their clothes. There was usually moonshine at these get-togethers, and on occasion a joystick would go around the circle. It's been the same in prisons since prisons were invented, I suppose. When you spend your life taking care of mudmen, you can't help getting a little dirty yourself. In any case, we weren't likely to be checked up on. "Clothes washing" was treated with great discretion at Cold Mountain.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'Right with Eversharp,' I said, turning Coffey around and putting him in motion. 'And if it all falls down, Dean, you. don't know nothing about nothing.'\par
