\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 'I hope so, too,' I said, and thought of John Coffey. I couldn't help it, John had said. I tried, but it was too late.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 I ate the eggs she'd brought, drank the juice, and pushed the toast aside for later. Then I picked up my pen and began to write again, for what I hoped would be the last time.\par
